<div type="definition">
<p>LOW LANDSCAPE BETWEEN NEAR MOUNTAINS.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The standard word for a valley is gǔ 谷 (ant. shān 山 "mountain"), and the word presupposes a certain size without emphasising large size.</p>
<p>2. Xī 谿 (later also written 溪 ) refers to a deep valley, preferably with a stream in it.</p>
<p>3. Huò 壑 (ant. fēng 峰 "mountain top") refers generally to a deep large and impressive valley with or without running water in it, as the season may determine,, and the word is rarely used to refer specifically to a given valley.</p>
        </div>
